weight per leg.

*Example fragment:* "Phase 1 weighting: consulting 60% / agency 20% / community 15% /
platform 5% / holding 0%. Platform + holding emerge in Phase B+ as Top Lists Partner
Factory + Korp-Startup model mature."

## §6 Anti-scope (what is NOT in this overlay)

Mandatory. Anti-scope keeps Layer 1 / Layer 2 split clean.

NOT in this overlay:
- Generic constitutional principles → Layer 1 (FUNDAMENTAL §1-§9)
- Anti-scope rules applicable across instances → Layer 1 §6
- Constitutional Lock content → `decisions/LOCKS-D*-ADDENDUM-*.md` directly
- Phase action lists → `decisions/JETIX-PLAN.md`
- Specific bet pitches → Type 10 `bet-pitch` instances

If a candidate-content fits Layer 1 better (sector-agnostic) → Layer 1, not here.
If a candidate-content is finer-grained (specific bet, project, OKR) → respective type.

